              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">Attain real solutions for current availability challenges. Based on a &#8220;DBA-centric&#8221; approach to High Availability, <i>Oracle Database 10g High Availability</i> concentrates on explaining Oracle Database 10<i>g</i> technologies and practices to database administrators, covering general availability, real application clusters (RAC), disaster planning and recovery, and distributed database solutions. Hardware and application needs are also taken into account. While Oracle Database 10<i>g</i> is the main focus, many of the options discussed are available in earlier database releases. Organized to provide conceptual understanding of High Availability, included are &#8220;HA Workshops,&#8221; step-by-step instructions to get you through certain implementations, plus real-world inspired case studies. </span>
              
