                    <span>Yes, Read this Book at least, twice. 
<br />
<br />Has steps linked to various chapters. 
<br />Reading, Second time will solve/Answer most of your questions.
<br />
<br />This Book is very good- I have implemented HA with RAC / DR - successfully many times.  
<br />
<br />On the scale 1-5
<br />
<br />RAC - 3
<br />Uses Oracle provided kernel (Linux) with firewire (storage) Architecture, for beginners it might be helpful.
<br />Missing GFS - Global file system implementation.  Can be used instead of ocfs.
<br />
<br />RAC - Oracle Installation - 4
<br />Installation, always read documentation from Oracle.
<br />
<br />Flashback - 3
<br />Since this is neat/new feature - need more explanation. Explains implementing Flashback, not much on administration of Flashback.
<br />
<br />DR - 5
<br />DataGuard - 5
<br />Very good steps and explanation - cannot go wrong implementing DR logical/Physical
<br />
<br />TAF - 4
<br />Good explanation of TAF - Yes you will be able to implement the TAF and load balance RAC env.
<br />
<br />ASM - 3
<br />This is a very powerful feature - Needs a separate chapter similar to DR/Dataguard.
